## Why these changes

### Strong typing & clear placeholders  
Named curly-brace variables separate **static instructions** from **dynamic user input**, making the task reusable while preventing accidental hard-coding.  This pattern is recommended for programmatic agents that inject runtime data.  [oai_citation:0â€¡Trafikverket](https://www.trafikverket.se/e-tjanster/boka-och-betala-korkortsprov/?utm_source=chatgpt.com) [oai_citation:1â€¡Trafikverket](https://www.trafikverket.se/korkort/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

### Early-exit & JSON output  
The booking API rate-limits clients, and Trafikverket explicitly asks users to release sessions quickly to avoid locking timeslots  [oai_citation:2â€¡fp.trafikverket.se](https://fp.trafikverket.se/Boka/?utm_source=chatgpt.com).  An early-exit design reduces needless navigation and protects against session timeout.  JSON ensures the calling code can safely parse results without string-splitting.  [oai_citation:3â€¡Trafikverket](https://www.trafikverket.se/om-oss/kontakta-oss/vara-forarprovskontor/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

### Exact-text selectors  
Trafikverketâ€™s UI labels (â€œVad vill du boka?â€, â€œVÃ¤lj provâ€, â€œVar vill du gÃ¶ra provet?â€) appear verbatim across all licence categories  [oai_citation:4â€¡Trafikverket](https://www.trafikverket.se/e-tjanster/boka-och-betala-korkortsprov/?utm_source=chatgpt.com) [oai_citation:5â€¡trafiktestet.se](https://www.trafiktestet.se/524/boka_korkortsprov?utm_source=chatgpt.com).  Selecting by exact visible text is more reliable than positional selectors, which often change when Trafikverket A/B-tests its layout.  [oai_citation:6â€¡Trafikverket](https://www.trafikverket.se/korkort/ta-korkort/personbil-och-latt-lastbil/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)  

### Robust location picker logic  
The â€œVÃ¤lj provort (0/4)â€ counter increments as each city is ticked; verifying that counter gives a free integrity check before closing the modal.  Trafikverketâ€™s help pages emphasise that a user may book at **up to four** test sites  [oai_citation:7â€¡trafiktestet.se](https://www.trafiktestet.se/524/boka_korkortsprov?utm_source=chatgpt.com).

### Human-readable time windows  
Using chrono-style expressions lets end-users type natural Swedish or English (â€œfÃ¶re 09:00 imorgonâ€, â€œnext Friday afternoonâ€).  Parsing those in code is trivial and removes rigid date-pickers from the prompt itself.  Trafikverket silently releases cancelled slots at random times â€“ checking broad windows catches those drops  [oai_citation:8â€¡Trafikverket](https://www.trafikverket.se/korkort/ta-korkort/?utm_source=chatgpt.com).

### Minimal scrolling + awaits  
Trafikverket injects rows via AJAX; un-awaited clicks often fail because DOM nodes havenâ€™t rendered  [oai_citation:9â€¡fp.trafikverket.se](https://fp.trafikverket.se/Boka/?utm_source=chatgpt.com).  The new ruleset makes explicit that every action must be preceded by an await on the relevant selector.









